  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Comparison between transperineal repair of rectocele with or without posterior internal
      sphincterotomy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Transperineal repair of anterior rectocele is performed in two groups of patients, the first
      will undergo limited posterior internal sphincterotomy, the second group will not have
      internal sphincteroromy. The two groups are compared regarding recurrence of rectocele and
      improvement of symptoms.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
